We have recommended the following:
Instruct their canvassers to require the prospective suppliers to indicate the brand names and other detailed item specifications;


Enjoin the BAC to conduct evaluation as to the most responsive bid based on brand and other qualitative aspect of the goods;




Direct the General Services Unit to prepare all the purchase orders entered into by the LGU and accomplish properly the P.O.s including the brand names and other detailed specifications of goods to be procured in order to serve the purpose for which the purchase order was prescribed.

Recommendations:

We have recommended the following:

Implement the accrual basis of recognizing revenue to conform with the Philippine Public Sector Accounting Standards;

Update ledger cards to show the unpaid balance at any given time and other relevant data; 

Execute lease contracts to all lessees of the Bonifacio Commercial Center and Bonifacio Public Market;

Revisit the Municipal Revenue Code especially on strengthening the collections of fees and charges as to encourage payment on or before due date; and

Exhaust remedies available to the Municipality in the collection of the delinquent accounts.

We recommended that the management:
Implement the accrual basis of recognizing revenue to conform with the Philippine Public Sector Accounting Standards;
Update ledger cards to show the unpaid balance at any given time and other relevant data;
Execute lease contracts to all lessees of the Bonifacio Commercial Center and Bonifacio Public Market;
Revisit the Municipal Revenue Code especially on strengthening the collections of fees and charges as to encourage payment on or before due date; and
Exhaust remedies available to the Municipality in the collection of the delinquent accounts.

We recommended that the management:
Require the LDRRMO and Municipal Engineer to coordinate with the proper National Government Agency for the infrastructure audit of the evacuation centers or selection of the suitable sites and proper design in case of building permanent evacuation centers, as the case may be;
Require the LDRRMO to take concrete actions on herein noted lacking facilities and the deficiencies noted in infrastructure audit, if any;
Require the LDRRMO to renew or update the registration of the rescue vehicle; and
Prioritize the utilization of the 70% LDRRM fund towards compliance of the above-cited circular, including the purchase of additional rescue vehicle in accordance with DBM Budget Circular 2017-1 taking into account the availability of fund and type of calamity frequently occurring in the municipality.

The management shall make representation with the depository bank through the Sanggunian Bayan on the adoption of the National Payroll System to distribute salaries via ATM to promote operational efficiency and to avoid robbery or theft;

Direct the Municipal Treasurer to generally pay its transactions through issuance of checks or Authority to Debit Account and to ensure that cash advances are granted in accordance with law;

Advise the Disbursing Officer to ensure that cash advance transactions are within her maximum cash accountability, otherwise, designate another personnel as Special Disbursing Officer if the nature and amount of the transaction so warrant; and

Advise the Municipal Accountant to record in the books the applicable cash advances account in consonance with COA Circular 2015-009 dated December 1, 2015 that prescribes the revised chart of accounts for Local Government Units which comply with the requirements of the Philippine Public Sector Accounting Standards.

Expedite the implementation and completion of the projects in accordance with the guidelines stated in memorandum of agreement with source agency for timely benefit to constituents;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to conduct reconciliation of records with source agency for proper recognition of fund transfer balances and full liquidation; and

Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to return to source agencies all unexpended fund balances on all completed projects, and for the Municipal Accountant to draw journal entry voucher to record the return as evidenced by the source agency’s official receipt, otherwise to request for authority to realign said balances for other priority projects.

Direct the Municipal Accountant to take up the following journal entries to reflect the above mentioned transactions;

Direct the Municipal Treasurer to enforce payment on the outstanding balances of the homeowners; and

Direct the Municipal Assessor to facilitate the issuance of certificate of title to the homeowners who has settled their accounts.

